          "Layer_Thickness_um": 40,
          "Scanning_Speed_mm_s": 1200,
          "Hatch_Spacing_um": 100,
          "Solution_Temperature_K": 573.15,
          "Solution_Time_h": 1,
          "Heating_Rate_K_min": 10,
          "Cooling_Method": "air cooling"
        }
      },
      "Microstructure_Info": {
        "Microstructure_Text": {
          "original": "Near-random grain orientation distribution with weak texture (max intensity 1.83). Fine equiaxed grains and coarse columnar grains observed. Increased number of precipitates compared to AF condition. Fine precipitates within columnar grains coalesced and grew to 72 nm (71% growth vs AF). Grain boundary precipitates nearly continuously stacked along grain boundaries (vs intermittent in AF). Al2Cu and AlCuSc precipitates at grain boundaries: 125 nm for equiaxed grains, 123 nm for coarse grains (8% and 5% larger than AF respectively). Nanoscale ring-shaped structure around equiaxed grains and strip-shaped structure along columnar grain boundaries. Despite minor coarsening, structures stabilized by nano-sized precipitates effectively impeding grain boundary migration.",
          "simplified": "Fine equiaxed and columnar grains with increased Al2Cu and AlCuSc grain boundary precipitates; nearly continuous distribution along grain boundaries; intragranular precipitates ~72 nm."
        },
